Amastra cylindrica.label: Amastra cylindrica
Amastra cylindrica.description: Amastra cylindrica is a species of land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the Amastridae family. This species is endemic to Hawaii. Wikipedia

Ancylus ashangiensis.label: Ancylus ashangiensis
Ancylus ashangiensis.description: Ancylus ashangiensis is a species of very small, air-breathing, freshwater snail or limpet. It is an aquatic pulmonate gastropod in the Ancylidae family. This species is endemic to Ethiopia. Wikipedia

Aplysiidae.label: Aplysiidae
Aplysiidae.description:
The superfamily Aplysioidea is a superfamily of mostly rather large sea slugs, marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Aplysiomorpha within the informal group Opisthobranchia.
This superfamily contains only one family, the Aplysiidae; the sea hares. Wikipedia

Amastra spirizona.label: Amastra spirizona
Amastra spirizona.description: Amastra spirizona is a species of land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the Amastridae family. This species is endemic to Hawaii. Wikipedia

Arca noae.label: Arca noae
Arca noae.description: Arca noae or the Noah's Ark shell is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Arcidae. It is found in the Mediterranean Sea and the Adriatic Sea from low tide mark to a depth of 60 metres. Wikipedia

Argonaut (animal).label: Argonaut
Argonaut (animal).description: The argonauts are a group of pelagic octopuses. They are also called paper nautiluses, referring to the paper-thin eggcase that females secrete. Wikipedia

Black slug.label: Black slug
Black slug.description: The black slug also known as black arion, European black slug, or large black slug, scientific name Arion ater, is a species of large land slug, a terrestrial slug in the family Arionidae, the roundback slugs. Wikipedia

Buccinidae.label: Buccinidae
Buccinidae.description:
Buccinidae is a very large and diverse taxonomic family of large sea snails, often known as whelks or true whelks.
True whelks are mostly marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neogastropoda. The family includes more than 1500 species. Wikipedia

California sea hare.label: California sea hare
California sea hare.description: The California sea hare also known as the California sea slug, scientific name Aplysia californica, is a species of sea slug, specifically a sea hare, a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the sea hare family, Aplysiidae. Wikipedia

Clea helena.label: Clea helena
Clea helena.description: Clea helena is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum, an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae, the true whelks, most of which are marine. Wikipedia

Cobcrephora.label: Cobcrephora
Cobcrephora.description: Cobcrephora is a genus of that resembles the Palaeoloricates, known from the Silurian of Gotland. Its interpretation as a polyplacophoran is widely challenged. Wikipedia

Cypraeidae.label: Cypraeidae
Cypraeidae.description: Cypraeidae, common name the cowries, is a taxonomic family of small to large sea snails. These are marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cypraeoidea, the cowries and cowry allies. Wikipedia

Conus tulipa.label: Conus tulipa
Conus tulipa.description:
Conus tulipa is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.
Like all species within the genus Conus, these snails are predatory and venomous. Wikipedia

Dorididae.label: Dorididae
Dorididae.description: Sea lemon is a loosely-applied common name for a group of medium-sized to large shell-less colorful sea slugs or nudibranchs, specifically dorid nudibranchs in the taxonomic family Dorididae and other closely related families. Wikipedia

Freshwater pearl mussel.label: Freshwater pearl mussel
Freshwater pearl mussel.description: The freshwater pearl mussel, scientific name Margaritifera margaritifera, is an endangered species of freshwater mussel, an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Margaritiferidae. Wikipedia

Giant clam.label: Giant clam
Giant clam.description: The giant clam, Tridacna gigas, is a clam that is the largest living bivalve mollusk. T. gigas is one of the most endangered clam species. Antonio Pigafetta documented these in his journal as early as 1521. Wikipedia
Length: 0 cm (At the age of two days)

Golf stick pearly mussel.label: Golf stick pearly mussel
Golf stick pearly mussel.description: Obovaria retusa is a rare species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. Its common names include golf stick pearly mussel and ring pink. Wikipedia

Hoplites (ammonite).label: Hoplites
Hoplites (ammonite).description: Hoplites are a genus of ammonite from the Early Cretaceous period. Its fossils have been found in Europe. Wikipedia

Helicoidea.label: Helicoidea
Helicoidea.description: Helicoidea is a taxonomic superfamily of air-breathing land snails, terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the clade Stylommatophora. Wikipedia

Limacidae.label: Limacidae
Limacidae.description: Limacidae, common name the keelback slugs, are a taxonomic family of medium-sized to very large, air-breathing land slugs, terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Limacoidea. Wikipedia

Lymnaeidae.label: Lymnaeidae
Lymnaeidae.description:
Lymnaeidae is a taxonomic family of small to large air-breathing freshwater snails, aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks, that belong to the clade Hygrophila.
Lymnaeidae is the only family within the superfamily Lymnaeoidea. Wikipedia

Mytilus (genus).label: Mytilus
Mytilus (genus).description: Mytilus is a cosmopolitan genus of medium to large-sized edible saltwater mussels, marine bivalve molluscs in the family Mytilidae. Wikipedia

Nudibranch.label: Nudibranch
Nudibranch.description: A nudibranch is a member of Nudibranchia, a group of soft-bodied, marine gastropod mollusks which shed their shell after their larval stage. They are noted for their often extraordinary colors and striking forms. Wikipedia

Oxyloma elegans.label: Oxyloma elegans
Oxyloma elegans.description: Oxyloma elegans is a species of small European land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk belonging to the family Succineidae, the amber snails. Wikipedia

Octopodidae.label: Octopodidae
Octopodidae.description: Octopodidae is the family containing the majority of known octopus species. Wikipedia

Pectinidae.label: Pectinidae
Pectinidae.description: The Pectinidae, common name scallops, are a family of saltwater bivalve mollusks. They are hermaphrodites, and the male gonads mature first. Wikipedia

Physella acuta.label: Physella acuta
Physella acuta.description: Physella acuta is a species of small, left-handed or sinistral, air-breathing freshwater snail, an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae. Wikipedia

Planorbarius corneus.label: Planorbarius corneus
Planorbarius corneus.description: Planorbarius corneus, common name the great ramshorn, is a relatively large species of air-breathing freshwater snail, an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae, the ram's horn ... Wikipedia

Pomatias elegans.label: Pomatias elegans
Pomatias elegans.description: Pomatias elegans, common name the round-mouthed snail, is a species of small land snail with an operculum, a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiidae within the superfamily Littorinoidea, the winkles and their allies. Wikipedia

Pondoland cannibal snail.label: Pondoland cannibal snail
Pondoland cannibal snail.description: The Pondoland cannibal snail, scientific name Natalina beyrichi, is a species of medium-sized predatory air-breathing land snail, a carnivorous terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae. Wikipedia

Ranellidae.label: Ranellidae
Ranellidae.description: Ranellidae, common name the triton shells or tritons, is a taxonomic family of small to very large predatory sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Littorinimorpha. Wikipedia

Sea butterfly.label: Sea butterfly
Sea butterfly.description: Sea butterflies, scientific name Thecosomata, are a taxonomic suborder of small pelagic swimming sea snails. These are holoplanktonic opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the informal group Opisthobranchia. Wikipedia

Sepia apama.label: Sepia apama
Sepia apama.description: Sepia apama, also known as the Australian giant cuttlefish, is the world's largest cuttlefish species, growing to 50 cm in mantle length and over 10.5 kg in weight. Wikipedia

Sepiola rondeleti.label: Sepiola rondeleti
Sepiola rondeleti.description: Sepiola rondeleti, also known as the Dwarf Bobtail, is a species of bobtail squid native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean and the Mediterranean Sea, including the Strait of Sicily, Aegean Sea, Adriatic Sea, Sea of Marmara, and Levantine Sea. Wikipedia

Smooth clam.label: Smooth clam
Smooth clam.description: The smooth clam, Callista chione, is a rather large, temperate, marine, bivalve mollusc that inhabits sandy bottoms or with small pebbles in clean waters down to about 200 m from the British Isles to the Mediterranean. Wikipedia

Solariella.label: Solariella
Solariella.description: Solariella is a genus of small to minute sea snails, marine gastropod molluscs in the family Solariellidae within the superfamily Trochoidea, the top snails, turban snails and their allies. Wikipedia

Solenidae.label: Solenidae
Solenidae.description: Solenidae, commonly called "razor shells," is a family of marine bivalve mollusks in the unassigned Euheterodonta. Wikipedia

Swan mussel.label: Swan mussel
Swan mussel.description: The swan mussel, Anodonta cygnea, is a large species of freshwater mussel, an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. Wikipedia

Succinea putris.label: Succinea putris
Succinea putris.description: Succinea putris is a species of small air-breathing land snail in the family Succineidae, the amber snails. Wikipedia

Swollen river mussel.label: Swollen river mussel
Swollen river mussel.description: The swollen river mussel, scientific name Unio tumidus, is a species of freshwater mussel, an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. Wikipedia

Thiaridae.label: Thiaridae
Thiaridae.description: Thiaridae, common name thiarids, is a family of tropical freshwater snails with an operculum, aquatic gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cerithioidea. Wikipedia

Turritella communis.label: Turritella communis
Turritella communis.description: Turritella communis, common name the "common tower shell" is a species of medium-sized sea snails with an operculum, marine gastropod mollusks in the family Turritellidae. Wikipedia

Unionoida.label: Unionoida
Unionoida.description: Unionoida is an monophyletic order of freshwater mussels, aquatic bivalve mollusks. The order includes most of the larger freshwater mussels, including the freshwater pearl mussels. Wikipedia

Warty venus.label: Warty venus
Warty venus.description: The warty venus, Venus verrucosa, is a species of saltwater clam. They are marine bivalve molluscs in the family Veneridae, sometimes known as the Venus clams. Wikipedia

Zonitoides nitidus.label: Zonitoides nitidus
Zonitoides nitidus.description:
Zonitoides nitidus is a species of small, air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Gastrodontidae.
Zonitoides nitidus is the type species of the genus Zonitoides. Wikipedia

Alabama moccasinshell.label: Alabama moccasinshell
Alabama moccasinshell.description: The Alabama moccasinshell is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. It is native to Alabama, Mississippi, Georgia, Tennessee, and possibly Florida. It is a federally listed threatened species of the United States. Wikipedia

Allonautilus scrobiculatus.label: Allonautilus scrobiculatus
Allonautilus scrobiculatus.description: Allonautilus scrobiculatus, also known as the crusty nautilus, is a species of nautilus native to the waters around New Guinea, specifically New Britain and Milne Bay, and the Solomon Islands. Wikipedia

Chamelea gallina.label: Chamelea gallina
Chamelea gallina.description: Chamelea gallina is a species of small saltwater clam, a marine bivalve in the family Veneridae, the venus clams. Wikipedia

Coosa moccasinshell.label: Coosa moccasinshell
Coosa moccasinshell.description: The Coosa moccasinshell is a rare species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. This aquatic bivalve mollusk is native to Georgia and Tennessee in the United States, and has been extirpated from the state of Alabama. Wikipedia

Cumberland monkeyface pearly mussel.label: Cumberland monkeyface pearly mussel
Cumberland monkeyface pearly mussel.description: The Cumberland monkeyface pearly mussel or Cumberland monkeyface, scientific name Quadrula intermedia, is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. Wikipedia

Dromedary naiad.label: Dromedary naiad
Dromedary naiad.description: The dromedary naiad or dromedary pearly mussel is a rare species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae. Wikipedia

Falkneria camerani.label: Falkneria camerani
Falkneria camerani.description:
Falkneria camerani is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicodontidae.
This species is endemic to northwestern Italy. Wikipedia

Fat Guam partula.label: Fat Guam partula
Fat Guam partula.description: The fat Guam partula or tree snail, scientific name Partula gibba, is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the Partulidae family. This species is found in Guam and Northern Mariana Islands. Wikipedia

Giant octopus.label: Giant octopus
Giant octopus.description: Enteroctopus is an octopus genus, many of whose members are sometimes known as giant octopuses. Wikipedia

Giant squid.label: Giant squid
Giant squid.description: The giant squid is a deep-ocean dwelling squid in the family Architeuthidae, represented by as many as eight species. Wikipedia

Grove snail.label: Grove snail
Grove snail.description: The grove snail or brown-lipped snail is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc. It is one of the most common species of land snail in Europe and has been introduced to North America. Wikipedia

Gulf moccasinshell.label: Gulf moccasinshell
Gulf moccasinshell.description: The gulf moccasinshell is a rare species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. Wikipedia

Helix aspersa.label: Helix aspersa
Helix aspersa.description: Cornu aspersum, known by the common name garden snail, is a species of land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Helicidae, the typical snails. This species is one of the best-known of all terrestrial molluscs. Wikipedia

Helix pomatia.label: Helix pomatia
Helix pomatia.description: Helix pomatia, common names the Burgundy snail, Roman snail, edible snail or escargot, is a species of large, edible, air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae. It is a European species. Wikipedia

Kimberella.label: Kimberella
Kimberella.description: Kimberella is a monospecific genus of bilaterian known only from rocks of the Ediacaran period. The slug-like organism fed by scratching the microbial surface on which it dwelt in a manner similar to ... Wikipedia

Narrow pigtoe.label: Narrow pigtoe
Narrow pigtoe.description: The narrow pigtoe is a species of bivalve in the Unionidae family. It is endemic to the United States. Wikipedia

Oegopsina.label: Oegopsina
Oegopsina.description: Oegopsina is a suborder of the squid order, Teuthida, in the Cephalopod Class. Some taxonomists raise it to the level of an order, in which case it is known as Oegopsida. Wikipedia

Opisthobranchia.label: Opisthobranchia
Opisthobranchia.description: Opisthobranchs are a large and diverse group of specialized complex marine gastropods previously united under Opisthobranchia within the Heterobranchia, but no longer considered to represent a monophyletic grouping. Wikipedia

Ostreoida.label: Ostreoida
Ostreoida.description:
The order Ostreoida includes the true oysters and a number of other related families of bivalves.
About 11 families are recognised within it, but suborders, superfamilies and subfamilies are used relatively heavily in this order. Wikipedia

Otala punctata.label: Otala punctata
Otala punctata.description: Otala punctata is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae. They are prepared in a typical dish in South Spain, "cabrillas", cooked in spicy tomato sauce. Wikipedia

Pecten maximus.label: Pecten maximus
Pecten maximus.description: Pecten maximus, common name the "great scallop" or "king scallop", is a species of scallop, an edible saltwater clam, a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pectinidae, the scallops. This is the type species of the genus. Wikipedia

Pod razor.label: Pod razor
Pod razor.description:
The pod razor, Ensis siliqua, is a coastal bivalve of European waters. It is edible and has been exploited commercially, especially in Spain and Ireland.
There is at least one subspecies E.s. minor. Wikipedia

Pulmonata.label: Pulmonata
Pulmonata.description: The Pulmonata, or "pulmonates", are an informal group of snails and slugs characterized by the ability to breathe air, by virtue of having a pallial lung instead of a gill, or gills. Wikipedia

Rio Grande monkeyface.label: Rio Grande monkeyface
Rio Grande monkeyface.description:
The Rio Grande monkeyface, scientific name Quadrula couchiana, is a species of freshwater mussel, an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae, the river mussels.
This species is endemic to the United States. Wikipedia

Tar River spiny mussel.label: Tar River spiny mussel
Tar River spiny mussel.description: The Tar River spiny mussel or Tar River spinymussel, scientific name Elliptio steinstansana, is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae, the river mussels. This species is endemic to North Carolina in the United States. Wikipedia

Stylommatophora.label: Stylommatophora
Stylommatophora.description: Stylommatophora is a taxon of air-breathing land snails and slugs, terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs. This taxon is currently considered to be a clade. It was previously regarded as an infraorder. Wikipedia

Trochoidea claudinae.label: Trochoidea claudinae
Trochoidea claudinae.description:
Trochoidea claudinae is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae, the hairy snails and their allies.
This species is endemic to Majorca, where it is known as Caragol de na Claudina. Wikipedia

Conus textile.label: Conus textile
Conus textile.description: Conus textile, common name the Textile Cone or the cloth of gold cone is a venomous species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones. Wikipedia

Discus ruderatus.label: Discus ruderatus
Discus ruderatus.description: Discus ruderatus is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Discidae, the disk snails. Wikipedia

Doryteuthis plei.label: Doryteuthis plei
Doryteuthis plei.description: Doryteuthis plei, also known as the slender inshore squid or arrow squid, is a medium-sized squid belonging to the family Loliginidae. It occurs abundantly in coastal waters of the Atlantic Ocean, from Argentina northward to North Carolina. Wikipedia

Ocythoe tuberculata.label: Ocythoe tuberculata
Ocythoe tuberculata.description: Ocythoe tuberculata, also known as the tuberculate pelagic octopus or football octopus, is a pelagic octopus. It is the only known species in the family Ocythoidae. Wikipedia

Mimic octopus.label: Mimic octopus
Mimic octopus.description: The mimic octopus, Thaumoctopus mimicus, is a unique species of octopus capable of impersonating other sea animals. Wikipedia

Longfin inshore squid.label: Longfin inshore squid
Longfin inshore squid.description: The longfin inshore squid is a species of squid of the family Loliginidae. Wikipedia

Seven-arm octopus.label: Seven-arm octopus
Seven-arm octopus.description: The seven-arm octopus is one of the two largest known species of octopus; based on scientific records, it has a maximum estimated total length of 3.5 m and mass of 75 kg. Wikipedia

Aciculidae.label: Aciculidae
Aciculidae.description: The Aciculidae are a family of minute land snails which have opercula. In other words, Aciculidae are terrestrial operculate gastropods. Wikipedia
